It's valid C to cast a structure to the type of its first element.  So in the example of<p><pre><code>  struct child {
    struct parent {
      int z;
    } p;
  } foo;
</code></pre>
you can access foo.p.z but not foo.z -- but you <i>can</i> access (struct parent *)(&foo)->z, so you can pass foo to anything which expects a struct parent.
